trend_summary: Across the series, built-up area grows steadily via infill estates and edge expansion. Housing clusters enlarge in the east and centre, while forests on the northern ridge stay mostly intact. Highway upgrades and a new sports/amenity complex accompany conversion of scattered farmland. The area remains green but shows moderate suburban densification.
notable_changes: New residential estate constructed in the eastern quadrant on previously vegetated land.
Central neighbourhoods show infill housing that tightens street grids and raises roof density.
Northern arterial upgraded with wider carriageways and a reconfigured interchange.
Large sports or civic complex appears in the south-east, replacing open ground.
Small farmland pockets converted to mixed residential and commercial use near the southwest corridor.
